                                         CAPE TOWN - A pensioner has been stabbed to death in an attack at an ATM in Mitchells Plain. It's believed the pensioner was drawing money at a fuel station. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana said: “A case of murder has been opened for investigation by the Mitchells Plain police after an incident that occurred this afternoon in a garage in Mitchells Plain where a 64-year-old man was stabbed and fatally wounded. No one has been arrested at this stage.”